    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-08-28T10:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-08-28T10:30:00-05:00" n="14"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d14">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.G Personnel/39: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wright</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-08-28T12:00:00-03:30"
                            >August 28, 1933—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. For the Secretary. The Foreign Office has telegraphically directed
                        Varela<note n="17" xml:id="d14fn17">J. Varela, Uruguayan Minister in the
                        United States.</note> to express the hope that you may head our delegation
                    to the forthcoming Conference and to intimate that affirmative decision by you
                    would undoubtedly result in attendance by other Foreign Ministers and contribute
                    greatly to the importance of the meeting.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
